Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.55,0:00:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you feeling, Mr. Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.68,0:00:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers, do you know who I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.56,0:00:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see my finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.60,0:00:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you answer me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.69,0:00:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.61,0:00:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Mr. Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.24,0:00:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,…coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.62,0:00:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming? What is coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.62,0:00:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Mon… coming…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.09,0:00:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster… is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.97,0:00:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.19,0:02:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Junkers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.32,0:02:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that you can talk already.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.78,0:02:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop pretending.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.90,0:02:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the four middle-aged couple\Nmurders in the past two years,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.12,0:02:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you were spotted near three\Nof the crime scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.41,0:02:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you have to say? Adolf Junkers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.67,0:02:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine. Suit yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.59,0:02:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that you are a lock-picker.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.84,0:02:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Your job was just to open the lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.81,0:03:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Slitting the victims' throat\Nin a single stroke
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.02,0:03:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is not something you're capable of.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.40,0:03:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,From that, we know that there\Nare multiple perpetrators.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.44,0:03:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe you need at least three people
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.32,0:03:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to disable the secured lock and murder\Ntwo middle-aged people without a struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.33,0:03:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We're almost done\Nlisting possible knife users.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.25,0:03:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only a matter of time\Nbefore I narrow it down to your crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.92,0:03:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you talk or not doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.39,0:03:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What I really want to know\Nis another thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.73,0:03:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you go across the country\Nto commit those four crimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.10,0:03:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you only kill middle-aged\Ncouples without children?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.03,0:03:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Although you did take\Nmoney and valuables,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.24,0:04:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,dividing those small amounts between\Nthe three of you isn't worth the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.99,0:04:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How about I make you a plea deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.21,0:04:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can testify,\Nwe will give you immunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.75,0:04:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Who solicited your services\Nto do the jobs?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.23,0:04:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers. It's over!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.98,0:04:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't question him any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.06,0:04:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No, just one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.23,0:04:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Please leave! I'm ordering you\Nas the doctor in charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.91,0:04:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine. I'll come back another time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.95,0:04:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But make sure he doesn't\Nget poisoned or disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.29,0:04:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I will keep him under surveillance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.30,0:04:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma. It seems to me that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.96,0:05:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,somehow strange things tend\Nto happen around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.38,0:05:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.30,0:05:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just kidding. Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.20,0:05:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Where do you think you're going?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.82,0:05:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going for a walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.99,0:05:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do anything without permission!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.33,0:05:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The patient needs fresh air.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.41,0:05:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just going to the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.21,0:05:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're worried, you can come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.30,0:05:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,-There!\N-Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.68,0:05:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is so warm and lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.06,0:05:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you can talk now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.19,0:05:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's this kind of day that makes me\Nrealize it's great to be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.44,0:06:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Without these times,\Nit's really tough to get by.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.11,0:06:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I see people live and die every day…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.95,0:06:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I think it's easier
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.45,0:06:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,for doctors to just think about promotion\Nor their own research.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.71,0:06:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I was like that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.09,0:06:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to get promoted\Nand do my own research.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.97,0:06:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Successful operations were just a way\Nfor me to improve my position.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.89,0:06:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,However,\Na boy's surgery changed the way I felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.98,0:06:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a twin. He was the elder child.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.73,0:06:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I saved him from a gunshot wound\Nin his head,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.69,0:06:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and it helped me rediscover\Na doctor's true duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.57,0:06:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,-All lives are created equal.\N-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.36,0:06:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,A doctor's job is to save those lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.41,0:06:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.71,0:07:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not too late to start your life over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.35,0:07:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.27,0:07:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Our ages are not that far apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.31,0:07:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But you talk like an old man,\Nand you saved my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.45,0:07:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm talking to my parent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.41,0:07:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly I have such a big child.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.28,0:07:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was little,\Nall I wanted was a cuckoo clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.42,0:07:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You know. When the clock strikes\Nthe precise time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.04,0:07:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,a nutcracker hops out of the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.22,0:07:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted it so much and\Nthought about it every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.84,0:07:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I pressed my face against\Nthe clock shop's display window.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.35,0:07:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the shop\Nwhere I first picked a lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.06,0:08:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I was arrested right away,\Nso I didn't get the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.07,0:08:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, I started working\Nas a lock-picker.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.32,0:08:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted that clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.58,0:08:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the only reason I did it… and now…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.71,0:08:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Just tell them everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.59,0:08:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell the police everything,\Nand then start over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.02,0:08:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,…killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.89,0:08:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,My associates were all killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.02,0:08:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,By whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.23,0:08:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it the "monster" you spoke of?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.41,0:08:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Today you have to get the girl\Nto go out with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.96,0:09:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I went through the trouble\Nto set you guys up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.25,0:09:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,She's the daughter of a state legislator.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.38,0:09:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,She is both beautiful and intelligent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.97,0:09:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to meet her to know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.68,0:09:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.64,0:09:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I should settle down just like you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.64,0:09:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Right? In your current position,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.35,0:09:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,not having a wife is… 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.27,0:09:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.40,0:09:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When the clock strikes the precise time,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.49,0:09:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,a nutcracker hops out of the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.66,0:09:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.21,0:09:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me! The clock in the window…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.21,0:09:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! What are you doing?\NYou'll be late to meet her!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.01,0:10:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not too late to start your life over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.16,0:10:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Officer? Excuse me, officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.70,0:10:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you're out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.17,0:10:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you everything, but can you\Nask Dr. Tenma to come as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.42,0:10:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.14,0:10:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.78,0:10:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to come in so late.\NCan I visit a patient?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.53,0:10:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Dr. Tenma. Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.74,0:10:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.66,0:10:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I found a great gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.80,0:11:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.51,0:11:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay…?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.18,0:11:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.48,0:11:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A candy?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.86,0:11:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.21,0:11:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.92,0:11:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just like that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.42,0:11:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Murders by poisoned candy,\Nand the disappearance of my patient!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.88,0:12:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just like nine years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.27,0:12:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.96,0:12:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.04,0:12:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me, Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.67,0:12:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.43,0:12:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.72,0:12:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get back to the hospital.\NIt'll be okay, Mr. Junkers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.89,0:12:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Don't come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.40,0:12:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot look at him, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.95,0:13:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,"Him"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.03,0:13:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the one who killed my associates!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.08,0:13:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll kill you too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.09,0:13:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Who… Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.55,0:13:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Doctor, you have to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.97,0:13:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Long time no see, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.93,0:13:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.31,0:13:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Nine years ago, you saved my life.\NIsn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.23,0:13:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Nine years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.86,0:13:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you already forgotten\Nabout those twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.41,0:13:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.58,0:13:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.63,0:14:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Those twins.\NI guess you do remember me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.64,0:14:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Run! You will be killed, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.31,0:14:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha… What are you doing?\NMr. Junkers is my patient!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.06,0:14:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.99,0:14:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an execution.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.99,0:14:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.95,0:14:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, please go! He killed the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.00,0:14:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.16,0:14:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We were hired by this man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.75,0:14:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He always called us on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.13,0:14:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,After each job,\Nhe would wire us a large reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.63,0:14:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd split the money\Nbetween the three of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.72,0:14:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You were the one ordering the murders\Nof the four middle-aged couples?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.60,0:14:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I got marked by the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.35,0:14:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so now we're in his way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.94,0:14:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Fritz the Slayer and Big Guy Boris
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.82,0:15:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,were already killed by him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.40,0:15:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Fritz told me before he died…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.49,0:15:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He said,\N"we've been hired by a monster!"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.79,0:15:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Killing people is nothing to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.62,0:15:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Run, Doctor! He will kill you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.04,0:15:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You talk too much, Junkers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.84,0:15:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.05,0:15:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do it, Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.97,0:15:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers might not know you, but I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.01,0:15:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.55,0:15:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I was your doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.68,0:15:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You are Johan Liebert,\Nthe elder brother of the twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.31,0:15:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the son of Michael Liebert, former\Nadvisor of commerce in East Germany,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.32,0:15:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,who came to West Germany\Nseeking asylum in 1986.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.36,0:15:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We know so much about you already.\NYou won't be able to escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.78,0:15:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't add another crime, Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.49,0:15:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"Johan"… I guess I used to have that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.58,0:16:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is not my real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.59,0:16:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What… What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.72,0:16:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No one could know about my past.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.64,0:16:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Not those four couples,\Nand not the Lieberts either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.85,0:16:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's different for you, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.52,0:16:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You saved my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.94,0:16:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You are like a parent to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.78,0:16:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,A parent… Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.28,0:16:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if it weren't for you,\NI wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.87,0:16:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.29,0:16:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't kill anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.04,0:16:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.12,0:16:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,"Why not"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.88,0:16:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think human life is?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.59,0:16:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I saved your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.80,0:16:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I remembered\Nthe fundamental duty of a doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.59,0:16:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I saved you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.38,0:16:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that all lives\Nare created equal!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.85,0:16:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No one has the right\Nto take another person's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.18,0:17:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I've lived all these years as a doctor,\Nkeeping that in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.40,0:17:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What's so funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.78,0:17:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor. I heard you became\Nthe Chief of Surgery after that incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.96,0:17:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so happy that you were promoted\Nto be the Chief of Surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.38,0:17:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it you want to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.97,0:17:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're here now because the Director,\Nthe Chief of Surgery,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.43,0:17:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Head of Neurosurgery died, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.56,0:17:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.77,0:17:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No… Was it you…?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.11,0:17:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You said it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.82,0:17:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it what you wanted?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.53,0:17:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,When I became conscious,\Nthat's what you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.66,0:17:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You hated them so much\Nthat you wanted to kill them. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.21,0:18:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't do anything wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.33,0:18:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,A man like that…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.00,0:18:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is better off dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.80,0:18:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,…better off dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.93,0:18:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I did as you wished.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.02,0:18:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor… I'm so scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.23,0:18:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Please help me, Doctor!\NI don't want to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.24,0:18:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.64,0:19:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I was supposed to have died back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.10,0:19:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You were the one\Nwho brought me back to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.10,0:19:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously, this rain is annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.39,0:19:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate it when it rains.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.94,0:19:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When it rains, it washes away\Nall the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.44,0:19:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How about you, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.16,0:20:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.96,0:20:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,From what you just told us,\Nthis is what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.63,0:20:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1986,\Nthe Liebert twins and their parents
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.84,0:20:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,came from East Germany for asylum.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.26,0:20:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Shortly after, the Lieberts were shot,\Nand the parents died.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.01,0:20:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The elder twin, the boy,\Nwas shot and severely injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.02,0:20:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You operated on the boy\Nand saved his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.69,0:20:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,However, surprisingly, the boy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.07,0:20:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,killed the Director, Chief of Surgery,\Nand the Head of Neurosurgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.65,0:20:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He did it with poisoned candy and escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.07,0:20:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Last night, he appeared suddenly\Nafter nine years.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.16,0:20:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He then killed a state policeman\Nwith poisoned candy again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.92,0:20:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,After that,\Nhe killed Adolf Junkers in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.42,0:20:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He is the one who hired Junkers\Nand the other two men
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.18,0:21:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to kill the four middle-aged couples.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.97,0:21:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is Johan Liebert.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.31,0:21:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Was that all?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.69,0:21:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hey.\N-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.53,0:21:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We can let him go today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.99,0:21:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you think someone\Nwith Dr. Tenma's credentials
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.21,0:21:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,would ever commit\Nsuch a horrible crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.00,0:21:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He has an alibi for the time\Nof the policeman's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.25,0:21:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't find any gunpowder\Nresidue from his hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.88,0:21:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we have no other clues to solving
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.93,0:21:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the murders of the four middle-aged\Ncouples anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.31,0:21:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we just look up this Johan Liebert
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.47,0:21:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and see what we can find out about him,\NInspector Lunge?
